			<h4>What if you refuse to take a chemical test in North Carolina?</h4>
			<p>North Carolina has an implied consent law. That means that if you refuse to submit to a chemical test you will be subject to a fine and automatic license suspension. Basically, this means that when you obtained a driver's license in North Carolina to with obtainting that license gave consent. If you have an out-of-state license, then your act of driving on North Carolina roads acts as your implied consent.</p>
